<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="b829ade6-4a16-547f-8993-5fde4c950bf6" activityNameId="96527a85-1b04-4467-a4ee-c373159d0a16" parentActivityId="4ede8db5-2903-4244-aa8f-d5d6c16d9fce" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">concrete production, 30-32MPa, with cement, Portland</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">ready-mix concrete</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">ready mixed concrete</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From reception of raw materials at the ready-mix plant gate.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends before the delivery of concrete at the construction site.
The dataset includes the whole manufacturing processes to produce ready-mixed concrete, internal processes (material handling and mixing) and infrastructure. 
The dataset does not include:
- the transport of concrete in a mixing truck. The combustion of 5.74 litres of diesel should be used to take into account the average transportation of 1m³ of concrete.
</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of North American 30-32 MPa ready-mix concrete. Density: 2"327 kg/m³. Ingredients (for 1 m³): Cement 297 kg, Water 160 kg, Gravel 1092 kg, Sand 722 kg, Fly ash 53.56 kg, Admixtures (air-entrainers and superplastisizers) 3kg. 30-32 MPa concrete is intended for non-structurally reinforced usage, exposed to chlorides and freezing and thawing (e.g. sidewalks, garage floors, porches, driveways, patio, curb and gutters) (following the Canadian CSA specs - http://www.rmcao.org/sites/default/files/CSA%20Quickspec%202012.pdf). </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Generic concrete mixes (cement, SCM, aggregate, water) provided by Athena Institute (unpublished data).Admixtures included in the mixes, as provided by the CPCI (Athena and Morrison Hershfield (2012): Life Cycle Assessment of Precast Concrete Commercial Buildings Cradle-to-Grave; Table 5). The 35MPa mix admixtures was used as proxy for 30-32MPa concrete.The average water consumption (not including batch water) is 65 L/m³ of ready mixed concrete. The average amount of water disposed is 35 L/m³. Water not discarded is recycled back into the process or into other products, and therefore not accounted for in this dataset. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Annual production volume of Ready-Mix concrete for North America estimated based on US production, and GDP ratio.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Distribution by ready-mix strength class estimated as:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">- 20 MPa = 20%</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="7">- 25 MPa = 40%</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="8">- 30-32 MPa = 15%</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="9">- 35 MPa = 24%</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="10">- 50 MPa = 1%</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="11"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="12">(coherent with distribution presented in http://www.ermco.eu/documents/ermco-documents/ermco_-statistics2008_091310.pdf (Table 3)</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="13"> </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="14">[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="15"> - concrete production 30-32MPa, RNA only, GLO, 2006 - 2006 (6ca130f3-06b0-404a-8f22-a737b7a9c971)]</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="a82c98c0-1e7e-495d-bad9-8b6d0d12e5c5">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Categories</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">construction materials/concrete</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <classification classificationId="27f6acbc-2350-450e-9762-1ce00e12ecba">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2395:Manufacture of articles of concrete, cement and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="aab06382-a476-4bec-a78b-d2fc0b849980">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">North America without Quebec</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">North American data. For some exchanges RER-modules have been used as proxy. Data quality indicators adjusted accordingly.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Typical technology for average North American production. Data quality indicators adjusted accordingly.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2006-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
